      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 1495: Re-accepting a tombstoned conversation clears `removed`/`erased` before the clone has completed. If the clone later fails, is interrupted, or the request is invalid, the local removal tombstone is lost and the conversation may appear accepted again without a valid re-invite completion. Consider deferring the persistent `addConvInfo(conv-\u003einfo)` until the repository has been successfully cloned, or preserve the old tombstone and restore it on clone failure. For example:\n```suggestion\n        auto oldInfo \u003d conv-\u003einfo;\n        conv-\u003einfo.created \u003d request.received ? request.received : std::time(nullptr);\n        conv-\u003einfo.removed \u003d 0;\n        conv-\u003einfo.erased \u003d 0;\n        conv-\u003einfo.members.emplace(username_);\n        conv-\u003einfo.members.emplace(request.from);\n        // Persist only after the clone succeeds, or restore oldInfo on failure.\n```",
      "revId": "39389aa320289813735010590f9402b28294e117",
